<div id="pf30" class="pf w0 h0" data-page-no="30"><div class="pc pc30 w0 h0"><img class="bi x0 y7a4 w1 h197" alt="" src="magfile/bg30.png"/><div class="t m0 x15b h198 y7a5 ffa8 fseb fc2 sc0 ls4a ws50">ELEMENT<span class="_ _f"></span>AR<span class="_ _4"></span>Y<span class="_ _5"></span> <span class="_ _9"></span><span class="ffa9">WORKSHEET</span></div><div class="t m0 x7a hf8 y7a6 ff2d fs13 fc2 sc0 ls0 ws0">48</div><div class="t m0 xb9 h178 y821 ff2c fse1 fc2 sc0 ls3e ws49">Working on the <span class="_ _6"></span>farm <span class="_ _6"></span>was easy </div><div class="t m0 xb9 h179 y822 ff2b fse1 fc2 sc0 ls3e ws0">for Min.</div><div class="t m0 xb9 h178 y823 ff2c fse1 fc2 sc0 ls3e ws49">The rain <span class="_ _6"></span>nally <span class="_ _6"></span>came.</div><div class="t m0 xb9 h179 y824 ff2b fse1 fc2 sc0 ls3e ws0">Min felt disgruntled because it </div><div class="t m0 xb9 h178 y825 ff2c fse1 fc2 sc0 ls3e ws49">was difcult <span class="_ _6"></span>to <span class="_ _6"></span>full the <span class="_ _6"></span>public’s<span class="_ _b"></span> </div><div class="t m0 xb9 h179 y826 ff2b fse1 fc2 sc0 ls3e ws0">desire for affordable rice.</div><div class="t m0 x15e h19a y827 ff59 fse1 fc3 sc0 ls0 ws0">Reason<span class="_ _30"></span>T<span class="_ _5"></span>rue / False</div><div class="t m0 x28 hf7 y828 ff2c fs4d fc2 sc0 ls0 ws0">‘Story Within <span class="_ _4"></span>A<span class="_ _5"></span> Story’<span class="_ _5"></span> is a literary technique commonly seen in stories, novels and even movie plots.<span class="_ _6"></span><span class="ff2b"> </span></div><div class="t m0 x28 hf7 y829 ff2c fs4d fc2 sc0 ls0 ws0">Do not confuse ‘story within a story’<span class="_ _5"></span> with a sub-plot. It is not. It is a standalone story that is found within </div><div class="t m0 x28 hee y82a ff2b fs4d fc2 sc0 ls0 ws0">another story<span class="_ _4"></span>.</div><div class="t m0 x28 hf7 y82b ff2c fs4d fc2 sc0 ls0 ws0">Consider the ‘story within a story’<span class="_ _5"></span> as the ‘inner<span class="_ _6"></span>’ story instead of an ‘outer<span class="_ _6"></span>’<span class="_ _5"></span> story<span class="_ _4"></span>. The ‘inner<span class="_ _6"></span>’<span class="_ _5"></span> story is usually </div><div class="t m0 x28 hf7 y82c ff2c fs4d fc2 sc0 ls0 ws0">the main story while the ‘outer<span class="_ _6"></span>’<span class="_ _5"></span> story is used to narrate the ‘inner<span class="_ _0"></span>’<span class="_ _5"></span> story<span class="_ _4"></span>. Usually a character in the ‘outer<span class="_ _6"></span>’ </div><div class="t m0 x28 hee y82d ff2b fs4d fc2 sc0 ls0 ws0">story is the narrator<span class="_ _4"></span>, telling another character a different story<span class="_ _4"></span>.</div><div class="t m0 x28 hf7 y82e ff2c fs4d fc2 sc0 ls0 ws0">It can also be the other way around where the ‘inner<span class="_ _6"></span>’<span class="_ _5"></span> story is used to bring across a point in the outer </div><div class="t m0 x28 hf7 y82f ff2c fs4d fc2 sc0 ls0 ws0">story<span class="_ _4"></span>. In short, one story establishes how and why the main story is told. Both stories are mutually </div><div class="t m0 x28 hf7 y830 ff2c fs4d fc2 sc0 ls0 ws0">supportive.</div><div class="t m0 x28 hf7 y831 ff2c fs4d fc2 sc0 ls0 ws0">Read the story ‘Growing <span class="_ _4"></span>Against the Odds’ on pages 20-22. Can you identify:<span class="ff2b"> </span></div><div class="t m0 x28 hf7 y832 ff2c fs4d fc2 sc0 ls0 ws0">1. the outer story?</div><div class="t m0 x28 hf7 y833 ff2c fs4d fc2 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. the inner story?</div><div class="t m0 x28 hee y834 ff2b fs4d fc2 sc0 ls0 ws0">3. the narrator?</div><div class="t m0 x28 hef y835 ff59 fs4d fc2 sc0 ls0 ws0">Y<span class="_ _4"></span>our T<span class="_ _4"></span>ask<span class="ff2b">:</span></div><div class="t m0 x28 hf7 y836 ff2c fs4d fc2 sc0 ls0 ws0">Now<span class="_ _4"></span>, using the above technique, write a composition of at least 1